#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:55
msgid "Differences Between In-person and Online Training Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:57
msgid "In-person trainings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:58
msgid "When watching videos, project them to the whole group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:59
#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:64
msgid "Assign (or let participants select) physical breakout groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:60
msgid ""
"Use physical sticky notes to get minute card feedback at lunch breaks and"
" end of each day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:62
msgid "Online trainings (a few small groups)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:63
msgid ""
"When watching videos, have one Trainer do a screenshare with their audio "
"on or have one person in each group play the video for the participants "
"at their site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:65
#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:71
msgid ""
"Use the virtual minute card form to get feedback at lunch breaks and end "
"of each day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:66
msgid ""
"Have participants do all small-group exercises with participants at same "
"site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:68
msgid "Online trainings (completely distributed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:69
msgid "When watching videos, have all participants watch separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:70
msgid ""
"Assign breakout groups randomly to breakout rooms in Zoom. Be sure to "
"remove Trainers and helpers when assigning groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:72
msgid ""
"Have participants screen share with their breakout room during the live "
"coding exercises."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:73
msgid ""
"For exercise to set up a workshop website, put participants in breakout "
"rooms and have one person screen share while the others help guide them "
"verbally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:75
msgid "Running a Teaching Demonstration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:77
msgid ""
"If you would like to watch an example teaching demo, there is a recording"
" of one here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:79
msgid "Before the demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:80
msgid "Sign up to lead demos."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:82
msgid ""
"For each trainee, pick a suitable starting point in the lesson that they "
"have chosen. Suggested lessons are available in the Instructor Training "
"Curriculum (under Extras). Do not have them start in the middle of an "
"episode. Note that some lessons (e.g., the Software Carpentry R lesson "
"using inflammation data) have supplementary episodes. Do not pick from "
"those."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:84
msgid "During the Demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:85
msgid "Go to the Zoom room. The link is in the Etherpad."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:86
msgid ""
"Once everyone is in the call (audio and video working), remind them of "
"the Code of Conduct, explain the procedure for the demo session, and "
"remind them that trainees have to be able to teach from any episode from "
"their chosen lesson. Ask whether anyone has only prepared for 5 minutes "
"from one episode instead of the entire lesson, and if so, suggest "
"strongly they reschedule. It can help to remind them that this is not a "
"high stakes test but a friendly opportunity for feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:87
msgid ""
"Ask those not presenting to mute their microphone, and ask them to give "
"feedback using the same positive-vs-negative and content-vs-presentation "
"rubric used in training. For a full session (5 trainees), they should add"
" feedback to the etherpad. If you have fewer people, you may choose to "
"have them jot down comments and deliver them verbally as time allows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:88
msgid ""
"Give the assignment to the first trainee, then give them a bit of time to"
" set up the demo (they may have to import some packages, load some data, "
"move to a certain folder etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:89
msgid ""
"Ask them to share their screen using the “Share Screen” lower menu in "
"Zoom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:90
msgid "Once they are ready, give them a 3-2-1 countdown to start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:91
msgid ""
"Use a countdown timer which makes a noise once their 5 minutes are up "
"(e.g., your phone), or just say “bong” really loudly at the end of their "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:92
msgid ""
"After the five minute timer, allow them to finish their sentence and tell"
" them time’s up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:93
msgid "Use a rubric to help you take notes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:94
msgid ""
"After the trainee is finished, first ask how they themselves thought it "
"went. If you have time, other trainees can give verbal feedback, or you "
"can summarize what is in the etherpad. Then, give focused, constructive "
"feedback based on your notes and the comments of others. You might choose"
" one or two things to particularly emphasize to help focus trainees' "
"efforts as they proceed to teach a workshop. It is also sometimes "
"necessary to take time to (gently) disagree with feedback from another "
"trainee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:95
msgid "Do NOT tell a trainee whether they passed immediately after their demo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:96
msgid "Repeat for the other trainees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:97
msgid "At the end of the season, ask for general questions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:98
msgid ""
"If all of your trainees passed, you can tell the group at the end of the "
"demo session. If anyone did not pass, tell everyone you will send them "
"each an email to let them know if they passed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:100
msgid "During the Demo (Troubleshooting)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:101
msgid "Refer to the Zoom guide to help troubleshoot connection issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:102
msgid ""
"If a trainee is teaching a Python lesson and their Jupyter notebook "
"doesn't start, direct them to http://jupyter.org/try."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:104
msgid "After the Demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:105
msgid ""
"Email checkout@carpentries.org with names, pass/fail, and SWC/DC/LC for "
"each of your trainees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:106
msgid "Clear Etherpad of data from your session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/trainers_guide.md:107
msgid ""
"Send each trainee an email letting them know they passed or did not pass "
"the teaching demo. If needed, let them know the reason they did not pass "
"and asking them to retry."
msgstr ""

